#DOC id=15--scheduler-posts source=/root/yvon/docs/briefs/lifeos-reference/15--scheduler-posts.md format=toon-doc compressed=2026-06-12T06:40:26.301Z

S|# 15 · Scheduler (Posts)|> The drag-and-drop calendar where ap posts land. Place posts across days/weeks to keep every platform's posting frequency fully active.
S|Purpose|"Schedule across every platform … a card → a slot → publishing operations center on a calendar." A powerful drag-and-drop posting calendar so the owner can ensure their **posting frequency is met across all platforms**. ap posts (from soc Approvals/Shorts) show up here and can be dragged into day/time slots.
S|Page header|- Title: **Scheduler**, breadcrumb `Vibe with AI / Scheduler`. // - Sub-line: "Schedule across every platform … publishing operations center." // - **Platform filter chips**: **All platforms**, **YouTube**, **LinkedIn**, **Instagram**, **TikTok**. // - Buttons: **Refine** and **Schedule next slot**.
S|Calendar grid|- A **week/day calendar** (columns are days, e.g. 18–24) populated with **post cards** in time slots. // - Cards show the platform, the post (e.g. "Convert the agt trend," "Shipping software in 20 min," "mem system breakdown") and time. // - **Drag and drop** to move a post to a different day/slot — the core interaction — so the schedule can be balanced and gaps filled to meet frequency targets.
S|Right rail|- **Failure triage** — surfaces posts that failed to publish (e.g. "A post that didn't go: needs the API auth … re-auth"), with **Diagnose** and **Create fix task** actions, and a **Reauthorize** button. Keeps the posting engine healthy. // - **Publishing engine** — status of the auto-publishing system, connected accounts, next scheduled post, and queue health.
S|Workflow|soc Approvals / Shorts "Schedule" → card appears in Scheduler → owner drags into the desired day/time → publishing engine posts automatically at the slot → failures surface in Failure triage for a quick fix → performance flows to **soc anl** (`16`).